40 /* Workaround clang bug:
41 
42  This macro expands to static if clang is used; otherwise it expands empty.
43  It is intended to be used in variable template specializations, where clang
44  requires static in order for the specializations to have internal linkage,
45  while technically, storage class specifiers besides thread_local are not
46  allowed in template specializations, and static in the primary template
47  definition should imply internal linkage for all specializations.
48 
49  If clang shows an error for improperly using a storage class specifier in
50  a specialization, then HIPBLAS_CLANG_STATIC should be redefined as empty,
51  and perhaps removed entirely, if the above bug has been fixed.
52 */
53 #if __clang__
54 #define HIPBLAS_CLANG_STATIC static
55 #else
56 #define HIPBLAS_CLANG_STATIC
57 #endif

60 #ifndef HIPBLAS_DEPRECATED_MSG
61 #ifndef _MSC_VER
62 #define HIPBLAS_DEPRECATED_MSG(MSG) __attribute__((deprecated(#MSG)))
63 #else
64 #define HIPBLAS_DEPRECATED_MSG(MSG) __declspec(deprecated(#MSG))
65 #endif
66 #endif
67 #else
68 #ifndef HIPBLAS_DEPRECATED_MSG
69 #define HIPBLAS_DEPRECATED_MSG(MSG)
70 #endif
71 #endif

73 /*
74  * Naming conventions and Notations:
75  *
76  * 1. Please follow the naming convention
77  * Big case for matrix, e.g. matrix A, B, C GEMM (C = A*B)
78  * Lower case for vector, e.g. vector x, y GEMV (y = A*x)
79  *
80  * 2. Specify the supported precisions for both rocBLAS and cuBLAS backend for any new functions:
81  * For eg:
82  * - Supported precisions in rocBLAS : h,bf,s,d,c,z
83  * - Supported precisions in cuBLAS : s,d,c,z
84  * Use the following notations,
85  * h = half
86  * bf = 16 bit brian floating point
87  * s = single
88  * d = double
89  * c = single complex
90  * z = double complex
91  */
92

117 #if __cplusplus < 201103L || !defined(HIPBLAS_BFLOAT16_CLASS)

119 // If this is a C or C++ compiler below C++11, or not requesting HIPBLAS_BFLOAT16_CLASS,
120 // we only include a minimal definition of hipblasBfloat16
121 typedef struct hipblasBfloat16
122 {
123  uint16_t data;
124 } hipblasBfloat16;
125 
126 #else
127 
128 class hipblasBfloat16
129 {
130 public:
131  uint16_t data;
132 
133  // zero extend lower 16 bits of bfloat16 to convert to IEEE float
134  static float bfloat16_to_float(hipblasBfloat16 val)
135  {
136  union
137  {
138  uint32_t int32;
139  float fp32;
140  } u = {uint32_t(val.data) << 16};
141  return u.fp32;
142  }
143 
144  static hipblasBfloat16 float_to_bfloat16(float f)
145  {
146  hipblasBfloat16 rv;
147  union
148  {
149  float fp32;
150  uint32_t int32;
151  } u = {f};
152  if(~u.int32 & 0x7f800000)
153  {
154  u.int32 += 0x7fff + ((u.int32 >> 16) & 1); // Round to nearest, round to even
155  }
156  else if(u.int32 & 0xffff)
157  {
158  u.int32 |= 0x10000; // Preserve signaling NaN
159  }
160  rv.data = uint16_t(u.int32 >> 16);
161  return rv;
162  }
163 
164  hipblasBfloat16() = default;
165 
166  // round upper 16 bits of IEEE float to convert to bfloat16
167  explicit hipblasBfloat16(float f)
168  : data(float_to_bfloat16(f))
169  {
170  }
171 
172  // zero extend lower 16 bits of bfloat16 to convert to IEEE float
173  operator float() const
174  {
175  union
176  {
177  uint32_t int32;
178  float fp32;
179  } u = {uint32_t(data) << 16};
180  return u.fp32;
181  }
182 
183  explicit operator bool() const
184  {
185  return data & 0x7fff;
186  }
187 };
188 
189 typedef struct
190 {
191  uint16_t data;
192 } hipblasBfloat16_public;
193 
194 static_assert(std::is_standard_layout<hipblasBfloat16>{},
195  "hipblasBfloat16 is not a standard layout type, and thus is "
196  "incompatible with C.");
197 
198 static_assert(std::is_trivial<hipblasBfloat16>{},
199  "hipblasBfloat16 is not a trivial type, and thus is "
200  "incompatible with C.");
201 
202 static_assert(sizeof(hipblasBfloat16) == sizeof(hipblasBfloat16_public)
203  && offsetof(hipblasBfloat16, data) == offsetof(hipblasBfloat16_public, data),
204  "internal hipblasBfloat16 does not match public hipblasBfloat16_public");
205 
206 #endif

208 #if defined(ROCM_MATHLIBS_API_USE_HIP_COMPLEX)

218 
219 #else
220 // using internal complex class for API
221 
223 typedef struct hipblasComplex
224 {
225 #ifndef __cplusplus
226 
227  float x, y;
228 
229 #else
230 
231 private:
232  float x, y;
233 
234 public:
235 #if __cplusplus >= 201103L
236  hipblasComplex() = default;
237 #else
238  hipblasComplex() {}
239 #endif
240 
241  hipblasComplex(float r, float i = 0)
242  : x(r)
243  , y(i)
244  {
245  }
246 
247  float real() const
248  {
249  return x;
250  }
251  float imag() const
252  {
253  return y;
254  }
255  void real(float r)
256  {
257  x = r;
258  }
259  void imag(float i)
260  {
261  y = i;
262  }
263 
264 #endif
265 } hipblasComplex;
266

274 #else

278 
279 public:

285 #endif

309 #endif
310 } hipblasDoubleComplex;

359  "hipblasComplex is not a trivial type, and thus is incompatible with C.");
360 static_assert(std::is_trivial<hipblasDoubleComplex>{},

366 #if __cplusplus >= 201103L
367 #include <type_traits>
368 static_assert(std::is_standard_layout<hipblasComplex>{},
369  "hipblasComplex is not a standard layout type, and thus is incompatible with C.");
370 static_assert(
371  std::is_standard_layout<hipblasDoubleComplex>{},
372  "hipblasDoubleComplex is not a standard layout type, and thus is incompatible with C.");
373 static_assert(sizeof(hipblasComplex) == sizeof(float) * 2
374  && sizeof(hipblasDoubleComplex) == sizeof(double) * 2
375  && sizeof(hipblasDoubleComplex) == sizeof(hipblasComplex) * 2,
376  "Sizes of hipblasComplex or hipblasDoubleComplex are inconsistent");
377 #endif
